# Module 4 Lesson 4 — Peer Review Relay Rules

> 本文件是 Cursor 项目规则，语义角色是约束模块 4 课时 4 的前端互审中转站、档案类型与后续后端互审接口实现；当课时 4 的状态机、API 契约、目录边界或实现阶段发生变化时，需要同步更新本文件。

Apply these rules when editing `src/modules/module-4-ai-info-detective/lessons/lesson-4/`, module 4 portfolio types, or `backend/app/modules/module4/lesson4/`.

## Course positioning

Lesson 4 is **题目卡互审与 V2 入库准备**.

It does not produce final published cards. It moves lesson 3 V1 cards toward V2 and prepares lesson 5 web trial.

## Development target

v0.2 implements the student peer review relay gate:

- A sends frozen V1 cards to target seat code.
- Backend stores request JSON and generates review code.
- B refreshes tasks, enters review code, claims task.
- B reviews both cards and submits review JSON.
- A polls/pulls review JSON.
- Gate passes only after A is reviewed and A reviews someone.

## Non-negotiable gate logic

Do not require mutual pair review. These two conditions are independent:

```ts
outbound.completed && inbound.completed
```

A three-student ring must pass:

```text
A → B, B → C, C → A
```

## State machine

Use:

```text
pending → claimed → submitted → pulled
   ↓         ↓
expired   expired

pending → cancelled
```

No additional state should be added unless it is strictly necessary.

## Timers

- pending expires after 6 minutes.
- pending can be manually cancelled by author.
- claimed uses a wider review countdown, default 20 minutes.
- claimed cannot be manually cancelled by author.
- submitted must not short-expire; retain until author pulls or cleanup.

## Review code

Use a 4-digit invite/review code. Reviewer may see task summary by seat code but must enter correct code before full cards are returned.

## Backend

Use SQLite and JSON text first. Do not over-normalize.

Minimum table:

```text
module4_lesson4_review_requests
```

Minimum endpoints under `/api/v1/module4/lesson4`:

```text
POST /review-requests
POST /review-requests/{requestId}/cancel
GET  /review-requests/inbox
POST /review-requests/{requestId}/claim
POST /review-requests/{requestId}/submit
GET  /review-requests/{requestId}/status
POST /review-requests/{requestId}/pull
```

## Frontend

Step 1 is a two-column relay station:

- left: my cards sent for review;
- right: tasks sent to me;
- top: two-condition gate status.

For this frontend-only phase, Step 2-4 must stay as locked placeholder pages. Do not implement Step 2-4 business logic until the backend integration phase explicitly continues.

## Boundaries

Do not implement:

- teacher dashboard;
- rescue mode;
- WebSocket/WebRTC;
- formal item-bank scoring;
- lesson 5 random quiz;
- Q score or frequency adjustment;
- final publish flow.

## Module boundary

Keep lesson 4 components in module 4. Do not export module 4 business components to shared. Reuse shared UI primitives only.
